The Bank of England said it forecast aliquidity shortage of around 300 mln stg in the market today.    Among the main factors, the Bank said bills maturing inofficial hands and the treasury bill take-up would drain 483mln stg from the system while below target bankers' balancesand a rise in the note circulation would take out 50 mln and100 mln stg respectively.    Partially offsetting these, exchequer transactions wouldadd around 355 mln stg, the Bank added. REUTER&#3;